flow of project :

Main (App.java)
   ↓
Spring Container (ApplicationContext)
   ↓
@Configuration (AppConfig)
   ↓
@Bean methods (Customer, Address)
   ↓
Dependency Injection (Customer → Address)
   ↓
Output

------------------------------------------------------
main class/starting point --> App.java

------------------------------------------------------
Setter injection is used to provide dependency AFTER object creation

Spring creates Address object
        ↓
Spring creates Customer object
        ↓
Spring calls setCustomer()
        ↓
Dependency injected

Why Setter Injection is Good
- Loose Coupling .
 Address doesn’t create Customer
 Spring injects it
 
 